Ctrl+U delete all the row

Ctrl+ w deletes just the last word

Ctrl+e go at the end of the row

Ctrl+a va go at the beginning of the row

ctrl+c to quit the process

ctrl+d or 'exit' to logut (or quit Putty in Windows)


to change user to user2:

su -user2

to reboot

sudo reboot


to list all the active process

top

If you need to load us keyboard

sudo loadkeys us

(it will work for just 1 session)
